    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-22T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-22T01:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Atomic/6–2246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-22T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 22, 1946—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1966. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> 1939, June 19.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d518fn14">Not printed.</note> Although no reference to contents
                    Baruch report has yet been made, Soviet press June 21 carries New <pb
                        facs="0780" n="766" xml:id="pg_766"/> York <gloss target="#t_Tass1"
                        >Tass</gloss> dispatch reporting that at June 19 meeting UN Atomic Energy
                    Commission Australian, Canadian, British, Chinese, Brazilian and Mexican
                    representatives announced approval by their respective govts of US proposals
                    advanced by Baruch, and that Gromyko presented Soviet proposal for international
                    agreement which would “ban production and utilization of atomic weapons and
                    provide for destruction of existing stores of atomic weapons”.<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d518fn15">For documentation in regard to the United Nations Atomic
                        Energy Commission activities, see <ref target="frus1946v01">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Bulk Gromyko’s speech is then quoted.<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d518fn16">For text of the proposals made by Andrey Andreyevich
                        Gromyko, the representative of the Soviet Union at the United Nations, see
                            <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi>, June 20, 1946, p. 4.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
